review_detailed_main:
I love this movie. it shows the real India that many claim(and dream) to have captured likes of slumdog millionaire(which are of-course vague attempts).

I could somehow recollect Udaan movie(co-written by same director) where the steel city Jamshedpur is the canvas. this time, it is country side of Danbad known for coal. the essence is that the struggle of life over generations remain same even as many reformers come and go. many (idealistic)changes meant for good of the society happen over generations and these are exploited (in reality) by the opportunistic. actors are handpicked for each role. the beauty of theater arts and story telling gets at its best.

if you are fedup with with srk, salman, akshay, ranbir, ajay, so on and so forth. this film is for you. if you have enjoyed DevD, this film is for you. go watch it otherwise save your money for another ra.two around the corner in your favorite multiplex :)
